      "id": "PopularPost227803",
      "post_content": "This is [Guardian Beast](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Guardian Beast) version 2.0. This was printed in Mirage, at a time when Wizards was \\*terrified\\* of hypothetical shroud abuse. They were worried that A gives shroud to B + B gives shroud to A would result in an unbreakable lock by turn 4 or 5, basically. This was in the days before combo decks could reliably produce a third-turn kill, when the [Stasis](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Stasis) lock was universally reviled as eeeevil. Black had [Guardian Beast](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Guardian Beast) and [Sinkhole](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sinkhole). White had [Swords to Plowshares](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Swords to Plowshares) and [Balance](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Balance). In theory, Spectral Guide could have tilted what was at the time a fairly delicate balance.  \n  \nIt took Wizards quite a while to realize it was perfectly alright for one card to protect another class of cards, that this could be normal (and was more natural for ![White](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=W&type=symbol) than for ![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol) as the core protective color; if Guardian Beast was printed nowadays it would have been ![Green or White](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=GW&type=symbol).). Compare to auto... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Salient",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost227803\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_post\">This is <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Guardian Beast\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Guardian Beast\">Guardian Beast</a> version 2.0. This was printed in Mirage, at a time when Wizards was *terrified* of hypothetical shroud abuse. They were worried that A gives shroud to B + B gives shroud to A would result in an unbreakable lock by turn 4 or 5, basically. This was in the days before combo decks could reliably produce a third-turn kill, when the <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Stasis\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Stasis\">Stasis</a> lock was universally reviled as eeeevil. Black had <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Guardian Beast\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Guardian Beast\">Guardian Beast</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Sinkhole\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sinkhole\">Sinkhole</a>. White had <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Swords to Plowshares\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Swords to Plowshares\">Swords to Plowshares</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Balance\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Balance\">Balance</a>. In theory, Spectral Guide could have tilted what was at the time a fairly delicate balance.<br/><br/>It took Wizards quite a while to realize it was perfectly alright for one card to protect another class of cards, that this could be normal (and was more natural for <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"White\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=W&amp;type=symbol\"/> than for <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Black\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=B&amp;type=symbol\"/> as the core protective color; if Guardian Beast was printed nowadays it would have been <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Green or White\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=GW&amp;type=symbol\"/>.). Compare to auto... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 227803)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '227803'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy67559\">Salient</span>\r\n                                (2/12/2012 4:30:31 PM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\